[start section id="20112"]

I carefully reviewed with Mrs. Hilliard and her husband the natural history of both colon and rectal cancer and their differences.  She has early disease, T2, N0 of high rectal tumor or rectosigmoid (stage 1).  There is no need for adjuvant chemotherapy, neither radiation therapy.  This was also discussed over the phone with Dr. Cody Lemus from Radiation Oncology.  The patient and her husband were very pleased with this recommendation.
We will see the patient in follow-up in about four to six-months together with Dr. Orozco.  I wrote the orders for this to be coordinated in a single visit to see both Hematology and Oncology.  CBC, chemistries, CEA, chest CT, and CT of the abdomen and pelvis were also ordered.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

