[start section id="20103"]

July 1, 2010:  Low-anterior resection for a T2, N0, grade 3 (of 4), high rectal versus rectosigmoid adenocarcinoma (negative margins and none of the 30 resected lymph nodes contained metastasis).
I had the pleasure to see Mrs. Hilliard.  She was initially seen by the GI Consult Team after recent surgery by Carolee Feder, N.P.  I will refer the reader to her excellent note.  Mrs. Hilliard has recovered from surgery without any complications and is up and about and asymptomatic.  A postoperative CT showed no evidence of evidence nor did chest x-ray.  CBC and chemistries are unremarkable including CEA.
The medical history is significant for large-cell lymphoma diagnosed in January 2000, had a CR with CHOP.  Later there was enlargement of a lymph node that biopsy showed to be follicular grade 2, which was treated with two doses of Zevalin, and since then she has been in remission.  She is followed by Dr. Orozco in Hematology.

[end section id="20103"]

